
This is the README for Sigschege, the SIGnal SCHEdule GEnerator

A software for creating timing diagrams for digital electrical circuits  

Subversion Id: $Id: $


* Requirements

ANCI C++ compliant compiler, standard compliant C++ STL

freetype2 library
 
transfig/fig2dev

Recommended: xfig


* Building from source (distribution tarball)

This project uses the standard GNU configure build flow. See the file
INSTALL for generic install instructions.

* Building from source (Subversion snapshot)

aclocal
automake --add-missing
autoconf
./configure
make
make install

* Debugging

Disable optimization:

make distclean
CXXFLAGS=-g ./configure
make

